JavaScript DOM

    - What is DOM?

        - DOM = Document Object Model
        - It represents the HTML page as a tree structure
        - JavaScript can use DOM to:
        - Select elements
        - Change content
        - Handle events

    In simple words:
    DOM allows JavaScript to control HTML & CSS

1.  Selecting Elements

    a. getElementById
        -  usSelect elementing `id`

        Example:
        let heading = document.getElementById("title");


    b. querySelector
        - Select first matching element

        Example:
        let para = document.querySelector(".text"); // class
        let btn = document.querySelector("#btn"); // id
        let h1 = document.querySelector("h1"); // tag


    c. querySelectorAll
        - Select multiple elements (NodeList)

        Example:
        let items = document.querySelectorAll(".item");


2.  Changing Content

    a. innerText
        - Changes only text

        Example:
        heading.innerText = "Hello Aadit";

    b. innerHTML
        - Can add HTML inside element

        Example:
        heading.innerHTML = "<span>Hello</span>";

    Difference:

    `innerText` → text only
    `innerHTML` → supports HTML


3.  Changing Styles

    heading.style.color = "red";
    heading.style.backgroundColor = "yellow";


4.  Events (Most Important)
    - Syntax
      element.addEventListener("event", function)

    a. Click Event

    Example:
    let button = document.querySelector("#btn");

        button.addEventListener("click", () => {
        console.log("Button Clicked");
        });

    b. Accessing Input Value

    Example:
    let input = document.querySelector("#inputBox");
    console.log(input.value);

\*\* Small Example (Mini Project)

    let button = document.querySelector("#btn");
    let heading = document.querySelector("#title");

    button.addEventListener("click", () => {
    heading.innerText = "Text Changed!";
    });


    - DOM connects **HTML + JS**
    - Always select element before using it
    - Events make pages interactive
    - `querySelector` is most used

